The paper deals with computational geometry, specifically the problem of covering points with axis-parallel rectangles. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algorithms and data structures, which are covered in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The problem of covering points with rectangles can also be seen as a combinatorial optimization problem, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper uses probabilistic techniques, which are covered in cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper involves optimization and approximation algorithms, which are covered in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
